### CSS Math Functions

CSS provides math functions for calculations directly in stylesheets.

---

### Calc()

```css
.element {
  width: calc(100% - 40px);
  height: calc(100vh - 80px);
  padding: calc(1rem + 10px);
}
```

**Rules:**
- Spaces around `+` and `-` are **required**
- Spaces around `*` and `/` are optional
- Can mix different units: `calc(100% - 200px)`
- Can nest: `calc(100% - calc(40px + 2em))`

---

### Min()

```css
.element {
  width: min(100%, 800px);
  /* Uses the SMALLER value */
  /* On mobile: 100%. On desktop: 800px */
}

/* Responsive font */
font-size: min(5vw, 48px);
```

---

### Max()

```css
.element {
  width: max(300px, 50%);
  /* Uses the LARGER value */
  /* Minimum 300px, but grows if 50% is larger */
}

/* Minimum padding */
padding: max(20px, 5%);
```

---

### Clamp()

```css
.element {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
  /*    MIN    PREFERRED     MAX    */
  /* Never smaller than 1rem */
  /* Preferred: 2.5vw */
  /* Never larger than 2rem */
}

/* Responsive width */
width: clamp(300px, 80%, 1200px);
```

---

### Practical Examples

```css
/* Fluid typography */
h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
}

p {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.25rem);
}

/* Sidebar with min width */
.sidebar {
  width: clamp(200px, 20%, 300px);
}

/* Full width container with max */
.container {
  width: min(100% - 40px, 1200px);
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* Card grid */
.card {
  flex: 1 1 clamp(200px, 30%, 400px);
}

/* Padding that scales */
section {
  padding: clamp(20px, 5vw, 80px);
}
```

---

### Round, Mod, Rem

```css
/* Newer CSS math functions */
round(2.5)       /* 3 - rounds to nearest integer */
mod(18, 5)       /* 3 - remainder */
rem(18, 5)       /* 3 - remainder (same sign as dividend) */
```

> **Best Practice:** Use `clamp()` for fluid typography. Use `min()` for max-width constraints. Use `calc()` for combining units.
